{"author":{"id":"daecaa79b752289d08fa06c7a65c8d0387caf00b7e262b5741f4805727d0a582"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1677963759,"nonce":"N8Odm1GRVNWcsYl3x9cOFh+C+Ng=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOCGKeh85Wt5-q","github-url":"https://github.com/git-bug/git-bug/issues/327#issuecomment-1454874538"},"message":"Maybe I'm misunderstanding something, but why wouldn't we be able to call out to whatever is configured with [`credential.helper`](https://git-scm.com/docs/gitcredentials#Documentation/gitcredentials.txt-helper)?\n\n```\n$ cat /some/git/config\n[credential \"foo\"]\n    helper = !/usr/bin/password-manager --flag1 --flag2 blahblahblah\"\n```\n\nI suppose this has the downside of supporting arbtirary executables, but fetching this information is available via `go-git` , and executing it (grabbing the output) is available via [`os/exec`](https://pkg.go.dev/os/exec) and friends.\n\nAssuming the configured helper is secure, this leaves `git-bug` with the same responsibility it would have if using some other backend; that is, ensuring that the received contents are secure and ideally zeroed-out or otherwise removed from memory after usage ([`memguard`](https://github.com/awnumar/memguard)?).","files":null},{"type":6,"timestamp":1677963804,"nonce":"Pwa2IlIaAM1gHM7guSC1ERnixbY=","metadata":{"github-id":"UCE_lALOCGKeh85Wt5-qzi4bzKE"},"target":"526d601be6b10e10b12c9183e0be3dfd5c4700b70085d5c2b328ec96d2f230fb","message":"Maybe I'm misunderstanding something, but why wouldn't we be able to call out to whatever is configured with [`credential.helper`](https://git-scm.com/docs/gitcredentials#Documentation/gitcredentials.txt-helper)?\n\n```\n$ cat /some/git/config\n[credential \"foo\"]\n    helper = \"/usr/bin/password-manager --flag1 --flag2 blahblahblah\"\n```\n\nI suppose this has the downside of supporting arbtirary executables, but fetching this information is available via `go-git` , and executing it (grabbing the output) is available via [`os/exec`](https://pkg.go.dev/os/exec) and friends.\n\nAssuming the configured helper is secure, this leaves `git-bug` with the same responsibility it would have if using some other backend; that is, ensuring that the received contents are secure and ideally zeroed-out or otherwise removed from memory after usage ([`memguard`](https://github.com/awnumar/memguard)?).","files":null}]}